      "title": "Bare surface composite (SCMap)",
      "description": "SCMaP is a specialised processing chain for detecting and analysing bare soils/surfaces on a large scale. Bare surface and soil pixels are selected using a combined NDVI and NBR index (PVIR2) that optimises the exclusion of photosynthetically active and non-active vegetation. The index is calculated and applied for each individual pixel.",
